      "shortest": true,
      "solution": "use std::io;\n\nfn read_f64() -> f64 {\n    let mut s = String::new();\n    io::stdin().read_line(&mut s).unwrap();\n    s.trim().parse().unwrap()\n}\n\nfn main() {\n    let weight_kg = read_f64();\n    let dose_mg = read_f64();\n    let conc = read_f64();\n\n    let dose = if weight_kg < 40.0 { dose_mg / 2.0 } else { dose_mg };\n    let volume = (weight_kg * dose) / conc;\n\n    if volume > 30.0 { println!(\"OVERDOSE\"); }\n    else if volume < 5.0 { println!(\"UNDERDOSE\"); }\n    else { println!(\"{:.1}\", volume); }\n}",
      "statement": "Calculate the volume of medication to administer to a patient.\nIf [[weightKg]] is less than {{40}} kg, [[doseMg]] is halved.\nIf the volume exceeds {{30}} ml, output {{OVERDOSE}}.\nIf the volume is below {{5}} ml, output {{UNDERDOSE}}.\nOtherwise, output the volume rounded to 1 decimal place.\n\n<<Rules:>>\n- volume (ml) = ([[weightKg]] × [[doseMg]]) / [[conc]]",
